      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The difference between a side project and a business is revenue. The difference between a business and a sustainable business is margin.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "revenue",
        "margin"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-difference-between-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best indie businesses are built on boring niches. Boring niches have paying customers. Exciting niches have Twitter followers.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker",
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "niche",
        "revenue"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-indie-businesses",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best SaaS businesses have predictable revenue. Predictable revenue comes from predictable customers.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "revenue",
        "predictability"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-saas-businesses",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to think about revenue is on day one. Not 'someday.' Not 'after we launch.' Day one.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "revenue",
        "planning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your business should be boring to run and exciting to bank.",
